<p>My application has a timer that allows me to detect if a device of certain description is connected to the PC. It works good even if I first connect the device and I secondly start the application. </p>  <p>However, when I tested it on an old Windows XP machine (AMD Athlon 1.00 GHz CPU &amp; 512MB RAM) <strong>and I first connected the device and I secondly run the application,</strong> it throws an Overflow Exception error and it changes the connection indication PictureBox image to a red "X".    I have to mention that if I first start the app and I secondly connect the device, everything works good.</p>  <p>Here is the timer's code (Interval 400ms):</p>  <pre><code>    Private Sub TimerWaitForConnection_Tick(sender As Object, e As EventArgs) Handles TimerWaitForConnection.Tick      Dim TempDevString As String      Try          FT_Status = FT_GetNumberOfDevices(DeviceCount, vbNullChar, FT_LIST_NUMBER_ONLY)         If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then            Exit Sub         End If          If DeviceCount &gt; 0 Then              TempDevString = Space(64)                FT_Status = FT_GetDeviceString(0, TempDevString, FT_LIST_BY_INDEX Or FT_OPEN_BY_DESCRIPTION)             If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                 Exit Sub             End If              FT_Description = Microsoft.VisualBasic.Left(TempDevString, InStr(1, TempDevString, vbNullChar) - 1)               FT_Status = FT_OpenByDescription(FT_Description, 2, FT_Handle)             If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                 MsgBox("Failed to open device.", , )                 Exit Sub             End If             handle_closed = False              ' Reset device             FT_Status = FT_ResetDevice(FT_Handle)             If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                 Exit Sub             End If              ' Purge buffers             FT_Status = FT_Purge(FT_Handle, FT_PURGE_RX Or FT_PURGE_TX)             If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                 Exit Sub             End If              ' Set Baud Rate             FT_Status = FT_SetBaudRate(FT_Handle, 115200)             If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                 Exit Sub             End If              ' Set parameters             FT_Status = FT_SetDataCharacteristics(FT_Handle, FT_DATA_BITS_8, FT_STOP_BITS_1, FT_PARITY_NONE)             If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                 Exit Sub             End If               If Mid(FT_Description, 1, 7) = "RÎ’-7800" Then                  FT_Status = FT_GetComPortNumber(FT_Handle, portnum)                  If techPermissionsOn = False Then                     TechnicianToolStripMenuItem.Enabled = True                 End If                 ChangePasswordToolStripMenuItem.Enabled = True                 FrmLoginTech.btnLoginTech.Enabled = True                 FrmChangePass.btnChangePass.Enabled = True                 btnReceive.Enabled = True                 MnuCommReceive.Enabled = True                 ToolStripReceive.Enabled = True                 If techPermissionsOn = True Then                     MnuCommSend.Enabled = True                     ToolStripSend.Enabled = True                     btnSend.Enabled = True                     MnuHelpFirmwareUpdate.Enabled = True                 End If                   If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                     Exit Sub                 End If                  FT_Status = FT_Close(FT_Handle)  ' Close device with Handle(i)                 If FT_Status &lt;&gt; FT_OK Then                     Exit Sub                 End If                 handle_closed = True                  If COMPort.IsOpen Then                     COMPort.RtsEnable = False                     COMPort.DtrEnable = False                     ClosePort()                 End If                  COMPort.PortName = "COM" &amp; portnum.ToString                 COMPort.BaudRate = 115200                       COMPort.DataBits = 8                 COMPort.Parity = Parity.None                 COMPort.StopBits = StopBits.One                  COMPort.Open()                   If COMPort.IsOpen Then                     COMPort.RtsEnable = True                     COMPort.DtrEnable = True                 End If                  picBoxUSB.Image = My.Resources.USB_cut_green_comple              Else                 portnum = Nothing                 TechnicianToolStripMenuItem.Enabled = False                 ChangePasswordToolStripMenuItem.Enabled = False                 FrmLoginTech.btnLoginTech.Enabled = False                 FrmChangePass.btnChangePass.Enabled = False                 MnuCommReceive.Enabled = False                 MnuCommSend.Enabled = False                 ToolStripSend.Enabled = False                 ToolStripReceive.Enabled = False                 btnReceive.Enabled = False                 btnSend.Enabled = False                 MnuHelpFirmwareUpdate.Enabled = False                  picBoxUSB.Image = My.Resources.USB_cut_red_comple                   Exit Sub             End If         Else             portnum = Nothing             TechnicianToolStripMenuItem.Enabled = False             ChangePasswordToolStripMenuItem.Enabled = False             FrmLoginTech.btnLoginTech.Enabled = False             FrmChangePass.btnChangePass.Enabled = False             MnuCommReceive.Enabled = False             MnuCommSend.Enabled = False             ToolStripSend.Enabled = False             ToolStripReceive.Enabled = False             btnReceive.Enabled = False             btnSend.Enabled = False             MnuHelpFirmwareUpdate.Enabled = False              picBoxUSB.Image = My.Resources.USB_cut_red_comple               Exit Sub         End If     Catch ex As Exception         TimerWaitForConnection.Enabled = False         If MsgBox(ex.Message &amp; vbNewLine &amp; msgpanelconnectionerror, MsgBoxStyle.AbortRetryIgnore) = MsgBoxResult.Retry Then             TimerWaitForConnection.Enabled = True         Else             picBoxUSB.Image = My.Resources.USB_cut_red_comple              MnuCommSearchPanel.Enabled = True         End If     End Try End Sub </code></pre>  <p>And the Overflow Exception Error window:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/M9CIA.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/M9CIA.jpg" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Why is this happening?</p>  <p><strong>EDIT:</strong> When I double click the app's shortcut to run, if I open another window before my app's form is shown and I let my app's form load in the background, <strong>then NO exception is thrown,</strong> even when I return to my app it runs good.</p>